contentrichtext.text: {{distinguish2|[[CACI]], an IT company based in London, England}} {{TOCright}} In general, '''Casey''' is a common variation of the Irish Gaelic ''cathasaigh'', meaning ''vigilant'', ''brave'', or ''watchful''. At least six different [[sept]]s used this name, primarily in the [[Counties of Ireland|Counties]] of [[County Cork|Cork]] and [[County Dublin|Dublin]].
